I79(2) Benefit ratio

I12An employer's benefit ratio as of any given June 30 shall be determined by dividing all benefits charged to the employer under paragraph (15) during the 12 calendar quarters ending on such June 30 by the employer's 3-year compensation base as of such June 30 as computed under paragraph (3).

I79(3) 3-year compensation base

I12An employer's 3-year compensation base as of any given June 30 is the aggregate compensation with respect to which contributions were paid by the employer under this subsection in the 12 calendar quarters ending on such June 30.

I79(4) Reserve ratio

I12An employer's reserve ratio as of any given June 30 shall be computed by dividing the employer's reserve balance as of such June 30, as computed under paragraph (6), by that employer's 1-year compensation base as of such June 30, as computed under paragraph (5). The employer's reserve ratio may be either a positive or a negative figure, depending upon whether the employer's reserve balance is a positive or negative figure.

I79(5) 1-year compensation base

I12An employer's 1-year compensation base as of any given June 30 is the aggregate compensation with respect to which contributions were paid by the employer under this subsection in the 4 calendar quarters ending on such June 30.

I79(6) Reserve balance

I12An employer's reserve balance as of any given June 30 shall be determined by subtracting the employer's cumulative benefit balance as of such June 30, computed under paragraph (7), from the employer's net cumulative contribution balance as of such June 30, computed under paragraph (8). An employer's reserve balance may be either positive or negative, depending upon whether or not that employer's net cumulative contribution balance exceeds the employer's cumulative benefit balance.

I79(7) Cumulative benefit balance

I12An employer's cumulative benefit balance as of any given June 30 shall be determined by adding_

I13(A) the net amount of the benefits charged to the employer under paragraph (15) on or after January 1, 1990; and

I13(B) the cumulative amount of the employer's unallocated charges for the same period, if any, as computed under paragraph (9).

I79(8) Net cumulative contribution balance

I12An employer's net cumulative contribution balance as of any given June 30 shall be determined as follows:

I18(A) Step 1

I13Compute the sum of

I14(i) all contributions paid by the employer pursuant to this subsection;

I14(ii) that portion of the tax imposed under section 3321(a) of title 26 that is attributable to the surtax rate under section 516(b) of the Railroad Unemployment Insurance and Retirement Improvement Act of 1988;ÿ1A\2\N and

