I89. Debentures and series A preferred stock

I19(a) General

I11The Association is authorized, in accordance with the provisions of this section, and such rules and regulations as it may prescribe, to invest from time to time in the securities of the Corporation by purchasing (1) up to $1,000,000,000 of debentures issued by the Corporation, and (2) after the acquisition of such debentures, up to $2,629,000,000 of the series A preferred stock of the Corporation.

I19(b) Purposes and procedure for investment

I11(1) The Association is authorized to purchase debentures and, thereafter, series A preferred stock of the Corporation at such times and in such amounts as may be required and requested by the Corporation in accordance with the terms and conditions governing such purchases (which shall be prescribed by the Association), to provide_

I12(A) for the modernization, rehabilitation and maintenance of rail properties of the Corporation;

I12(B) for the acquisition of equipment and other capital needs;

I12(C) for the refinancing of indebtedness which was incurred by the Corporation under section 721 of this title or which was incurred under section 725 of this title and assumed by the Corporation; or

I12(D) working capital as contemplated by the final system plan.

